# May Inspired Events ðŸŽ‰

A Laravel 10 project for event management, bookings, and role-based access (Admin, Vendor, User).

---

## ðŸš€ Getting Started

Follow these steps after cloning/downloading the project.

### 1. Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/kingotsima/may-inspired-events.git
cd may-inspired-events

### 2. Install Dependencies
composer install
npm install && npm run build

### 3. Set up Environment
cp .env.example .env
# Then generate app key
php artisan key:generate

### 4. Run Migrations and Seed Database
php artisan migrate --seed




## ðŸ‘¤ Roles & Permissions Setup

This project uses Spatie Laravel Permission.
Run the following in your terminal to set up roles:

### 1. Create Admin Role
php artisan tinker
# Inside Tinker:
Spatie\Permission\Models\Role::create(['name' => 'Admin']);
$user = App\Models\User::where('email', 'admin@gmail.com')->first();
$user->assignRole('Admin');

### 2. Create Vendor Role
php artisan tinker
# Inside Tinker:
use Spatie\Permission\Models\Role;
Role::create(['name' => 'Vendor', 'guard_name' => 'web']);



### Useful Commands

## Run local server:
php artisan serve

## Run queue workers (for jobs/notifications):
php artisan queue:work

## Clear caches:
php artisan optimize:clear